6:
And once you're riding those waves,
you just go south! Keep going and
going, and you'll run into these
things called Floats!
8:
S-so you're really gonna become an
adventurer? You're gonna leave?
9:
Ahaha! Not right away! My super
secret boat isn't finished yet. But
once it is, I'm outta here!
11:
And when that time comes, Floretta,
I want you to come with me...
18: Even the benches are the same.
19:
I wonder if Alaimi ever became an
adventurer...
24:
A blanket of snow and
white-capped mountains... It's just
as you described, Floretta. What a
beautiful place.
29:
I'm just as surprised as you. This
town really is the same as I left it.
34:
Now, how are we going to find your
friend? Her name was Alaimi, ri—
38:
You must be bad guys, right? Are
you pirates?!
41:
How did you—wait, I'm not a pirate
anymore! A-and I wasn't a bad one
to begin with!
44:
What are you kids doing?! Stop
bothering those tourists and get
back to the orphanage!
46:
Sorry about the kids. They didn't try
anything funny, did they?
59:
Wow, so you're a teacher at the
local orphanage. Were those kids
some of your students?
61:
Yeah, they can be a real handful,
but I was the same way at their age.
It's actually kinda cute.
63:
I'm more surprised by Floretta here. I
can't believe you became an
adventurer!
66:
A-ahaha. W-well, I-I've still got a
long ways to g-g-go before I'm as
good as everyone else—
69:
Ahaha! What's with that shaky
voice? You're not nervous around
me, are you?
72:
N-no waaay! Wh-wh-what makes
you think that?
76:
Um... Have you mostly stayed on the
island then? When did you become
a teacher?
78:
I started working at the orphanage
about two years ago. As for the
island... I never left.
84:
A-ahaha! You know, it's been a
while, so I think I'll go for a little stroll
around the ol' hometown!
97: Um... I made some baranki for you.
100:
Thank you, Floretta. Do you think I
could share these with the children?
103:
I don't know if there's enough for
that, but why don't you two make
some more together? You brought
the ingredients, right, Floretta?
107:
Phew, now we just wait for them to
bake. We can't really splurge on
treats in the winter time, so I'm sure
the kids will love this.
110:
We used to make these a lot as kids,
didn't we? We'd steal flour from the
warehouse and get scolded.
113:
It would've been around this time of
year too. We also used to make
them for each other on Fioletovy
Den, right?
116:
You always dreamed of being an
adventurer back then. You were
even building a boat in secret.
119:
But then... I collapsed in the snow,
and the villagers came looking for
me... only to find your boat.
122:
I... I'm so sorry... You weren't able to
become an adventurer because of—
125:
Floretta, I'm the one who needs to
apologize to you.
131:
I was pretty cold to you after that
day, wasn't I?
132:
I knew... You only collapsed outside
because you went looking for me. I
hadn't come home yet, despite the
blizzard outside...
133:
You risked your life to find me. That
took real courage. But instead of
being thankful, I was jealous of your
strength...
134:
You might think you're the reason I
never became an adventurer, but... I
don't think I ever had the courage
needed to leave this island.
137:
I was just trying to look cool in front
of you... I'm sorry.
145:
You've always been my hero, Alaimi!
I wanted to be just like you...
Th-that's how I ended up where I am
today.
147:
Even now, you're just as cool and
kind... and warm as I remember you.
149: Really? Well... I'm happy to hear that.
151:
Guess this is goodbye, right? Be
careful out there. I'm really glad we
could see each other again.
155:
U-um, Alaimi, maybe I could stop by
again next year for Fioletovy Den—
158:
No... I'll DEFINITELY stop by for
Fioletovy Den. 
And some other days too.
161:
So this isn't goodbye. 
It's see you later!
